Package: BVS.DAdj
Title: Bayesian Variable Selection with Dual-Adjacency Network-Informed
        Ising Priors
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Yubing Yao [aut, cre], Raji Balasubramanian [aut], Mahlet Tadesse [aut]
Maintainer: Yubing Yao <yyao@umass.edu>
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yubing", "Yao", email = "yyao@umass.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Raji", "Balasubramanian", email = "rbalasub@schoolph.umass.edu",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Mahlet", "Tadesse", email = "mgt26@georgetown.edu",
           role = "aut"))
Description: MCMC methods for Bayesian variable selection in logistic regression
    with Ising/MRF priors informed by graphical model adjacency. Supports
    Metropolis-Hastings and Polya-Gamma augmented Gibbs sampling with fixed,
    graphical lasso, and Bayesian GGM adjacency structures. Includes dense and
    sparse high-dimensional variants with single and dual network priors.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
